products.name: Samsung Galaxy M40
products.description: Samsung Galaxy M40 (Midnight Blue, 128 GB) features and specifications include 6 GB RAM, 128 GB ROM, 3500 mAh battery, 32 MP back camera and MP front camera. Compare Galaxy M40 by price and performance

products.name: OnePlus 13 Pro
products.description: Overview:Once more, OnePlus strives to give speed and photography the balance they both desperately need. Keep your expectations high with the camera output, with the partnership with Hasselblad that’s sure to deliver. It’s a device made for consumers who appreciate minimal bloat, rapid charging, and an ultra responsive screen.

products.name: Xiaomi Mi 15 Ultra
products.description: Overview: Shenzhen-based Xiaomi has designed the flagship for camera professionals, with pro-grade photography modes powered by Leica lenses. Considering the rapid charging and powerful internals, this flagship can remain an all-time favorite for visual creators and high-performance users.

products.name: Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 7
products.description: Overview: Samsung has been a dominant player in the foldable segment, and the Fold 7 is yet another from them. The enhanced durability of the hinge alongside the camera that’s concealed under the display shows just how advanced the tech is getting. This device is perfect for multitaskers and working professionals on the go.

products.name: Realme GT 4 Pro
products.description: Overview: Focused on gamers and heavy users, the GT 4 Pro provides speed along with smooth visuals due to its 144Hz display. The value provided makes it a wise selection for budget seekers, especially with the price vs performance ratio.

products.name: Google Pixel 10 Pro
products.description: Overview: When compared to other smartphone brands, Pixel devices stand out thanks to their software-first approach. The Pixel 10 Pro is rumored to offer even more AI features for voice commands, photos, and multitasking. A streamlined UI combined with extended software support remain unbeatable selling points for the Pixel lineup

products.name: Nothing Phone (3)
products.description: Overview: Nothing focuses on the user experience and performance with Phone (3). Though not a flagship killer, the Phone (3) retains the brand's signature design, great for users seeking a visually striking device that performs well for daily tasks.
